     src="/images/1-300x300.jpg" alt="" width="300"                        height="300"                        sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px"></p>                <h2>1963</h2>                <h3>First significant discovery</h3>                <p>Santos made its first significant discovery of natural gas in the Cooper Basin with the Gidgealpa 2                  well in 1963. The Moomba 1 discovery in 1966 confirmed this region as a major petroleum province. As a                  result, Santos had a commercially viable quantity of gas and entered into gas sales agreements with                  the South Australian Gas Company, the Electricity Trust of South Australia and the Australian Gas                  Light Company. Gas supplies commenced in 1969.</p>              </div>              <div class="col-lg-4">                <p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-11537"                        src="/images/2-300x300.jpg" alt="" width="300"                        height="300"                        sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px"></p>                <h2>1980s</h2>                <h3>Tirrawarra discovery</h3>                <p>The 1980s saw Santos develop a major liquids business following the discovery of oil at Tirrawarra in                  central Australia in the early 1970s.</p>                <p>A liquids recovery plant was built at Moomba, South Australia along with a fractionation and load-out                  facility at Port Bonython.</p>              </div>              <div class="col-lg-4">                <p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-11541"                        src="/images/3-300x300.jpg" alt="" width="300"                        height="300"                        sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px"></p>                <h2>1990s</h2>                <h3>Major Australian enterprise</h3>                <p>A number of acquisitions in the 1990s provided Santos with additional opportunities onshore and                  offshore Australia, Indonesia, Malaysia, Vietnam and Papua New Guinea.</p>                <p>By the 1990s Santos had become a major Australian operating enterprise with interests in United                  States and United Kingdom petroleum provinces and in emerging areas such as the Timor Sea and Western                  Australia.</p>              </div>            </div>          </section>          <section class="three-column-row" data-sectionid="3">            <div class="row">              <div class="col-lg-4">                <p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-11544"                        src="/images/4-300x300.jpg" alt="" width="300"                        height="300"                        sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px"></p>                <h2>2011</h2>                <h3>First production of LNG</h3>                <p>In 2011 the Santos GLNG project was sanctioned. First production of LNG was announced on 24 September                  2015.</p>                <p>The first shipment of LNG left Curtis Island on 16 October 2015 and was delivered in South Korea on                  28 October 2015.</p>              </div>              <div class="col-lg-4">                <p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-11546"                        src="/images/5-300x300.png" alt="" width="300"                        height="300"                        sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px"></p>                <h2>2014</h2>                <h3>Celebrating 60 years</h3>                <p>In 2014, Santos celebrated 60 years since being incorporated on 18 March 1954.</p>              </div>              <div class="col-lg-4">                <p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-11551"                        src="/images/6-300x300.jpg" alt="" width="300"                        height="300"                        sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px"></p>                <h2>2019</h2>                <h3>50 years of natural gas supply</h3>                <p>2019 marked 50 years since the first gas from Santos’ operations in the Cooper Basin made its way to                  homes and businesses in Adelaide.</p>              </div>            </div>          </section>          <section class="three-column-row" data-sectionid="4">            <div class="row">              <div class="col-lg-4">                <p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-11555"                        src="/images/7-300x300.jpg" alt="" width="300"                        height="300"                        sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px"></p>                <h2>2021</h2>                <h3>A regional champion</h3>                <p>Santos completed a merger with Oil Search Limited, combining two industry leaders and enhancing the                  company’s growth portfolio and Papua New Guinea operating business.</p>              </div>              <div class="col-lg-4">              </div>              <div class="col-lg-4">              </div>            </div>          </section>          <section class="one-column-row visible-xs hidden-xs visible-sm hidden-sm d-md-none d-none d-md-block"                   data-sectionid="5">            <div class="one-col-inner-wrp ">              <div class="video-img-wrapper left">                <figure class="video-img-area no-info">                  <a href="//youtube.com/embed/M2K9qDEMQA4?rel=0&amp;modestbranding=0&amp;showinfo=0&amp;autohide=1&amp;autoplay=1"                     class="video-img" data-rel="lightcase">                    <div class="video-image-wrp"                         style="background-image: url('/images/core-assets-banner-826x464.jpg')">        